item.dc:creator: @Darth_Afro56 Darth_Afro56
item.description:
@Darth_Afro56 wrote:

Heres an example of some commands.

else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("ibans") && playerRights >= 1)<--- This means only Mods can use it. { addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1);<-----All these mean the Adding an Item to the Inventory in this case Na iban Staff. addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1); addItem(1409, 1); sendMessage("Finnally! HAVE YOUR IBAN STAFFS FFS!");<---This sends a message when you execute the command. }

else if (command.startsWith("empty")) { removeAllItems();<-------- This is a void that you use in this case it removes your items in Inventory! }

else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("wildmine")) if(absY >= 3672)<------This tell if the player is above 20 wildy. { sendMessage("You cannot teleport above level 20 wilderness.");<---Send message } else <----- If the player is not above 20 Wildy. { teleportToX = 3081;<------ Teleports to coordinate X teleportToY = 3762;<------ Teleports to Coordinate Y sendMessage("Lots of rocks!"); <---- sends message. }

Well those are some basic commands
